# React / TypeScript Standards

## TypeScript Config (required)
`tsconfig.json` must have `strict: true`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`, `noImplicitReturns: true`.
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define a proper type.
- No `@ts-ignore` — fix the type instead.

## API Layer
- All `fetch()` calls live in `src/api/*.ts` — never inside components or hooks.
- `src/api/types.ts` mirrors every backend Pydantic model (single source of truth for shared types).
- SSE streaming via `AsyncGenerator<string>` — not WebSocket.

```typescript
// ✅ api layer owns network
export async function* streamChat(req: ChatRequest): AsyncGenerator<string> { ... }

// ❌ fetch inside a component
const resp = await fetch("/api/chat", ...);  // inside ChatWindow — forbidden
```

## Components
- One responsibility per component — render only; no business logic in JSX.
- Props typed with `interface Props` — never `any`.
- Every async-boundary component needs an error boundary parent.

## Hooks
- Business logic lives in `src/hooks/use*.ts` — not in components.
- Return a typed object, not a positional tuple (unless exactly 2 items).
- Hooks must not import from `src/components/` (prevents circular deps).

```typescript
// ✅ hook owns state; component owns rendering
const { messages, sendMessage, isStreaming } = useChat();
```

## Module Layout
```
frontend/src/
  api/          types.ts + one file per endpoint
  components/   ChatWindow, MessageBubble, Sidebar, FileUpload
  hooks/        useChat, useModels, useTheme
  utils/        pure helpers (markdown, formatting)
  styles/       theme.css (CSS vars), global.css
  App.tsx
```

## Theme
Light/Dark via CSS variables on `<html data-theme>` — instant toggle, no page reload, no localStorage hacks.
